The paper presents a deep learning system for predicting the histochemical score of breast cancer TMA images. This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The system uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are a popular machine learning technique, and the paper discusses the architecture and training of these networks, indicating relevance to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also involves image processing and analysis, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
